{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox film |name=A Woman's Case |film name='''מקרה אישה''' |image=A Woman's Case.jpg |caption=[[DVD]] cover |director=[[Jacques Katmor]] |writer={{Flat list| *[[Jacques Katmor]] *[[Amnon Salomon]]}} |producer={{Flat list| *{{ill|Avraham Deshe|he|אברהם דשא (פשנל)}} *Mati Raz}} |music={{Flat list| *[[The Churchills]] *{{ill|Yohanan Zaray|he|יוחנן זראי}}}} |starring={{Flat list| *{{ill|Helit Yeshurun|he|הלית ישורון}} *Yossi Spector *[[Igael Tumarkin]] *Ann Tochmeyer *Tirzeh Arbel *Adar Eshet *{{ill|Aharon Almog|he|אהרון אלמוג (שחקן)}} *Aviva Paz *{{ill|Gad Kaynar|he|גד קינר|de|Gad Kaynar|no}} *{{ill|Ika Yisraeli|he|איקא ישראלי}} *Abraham Plata *Ester Zbako *Anat Zagórski *Avraham Inhaber *Nora Jantzen *Smadar Dror *Daniella Doron *Tatiana Lifshitz *Joseph Ben-Gal *Rachel Efrati *Margaret Gary *Ester Safkow *Ahuva Zimmerman *Susie Hulk *Els Salla *Urs Plang *Nitza Ernst *{{ill|Raquel Shore|he|רחל שור}} *Yael Grinfeld *Rachel Levy *Gila Peles *Cornelia Kristal}} |cinematography=[[Amnon Salomon]] |editing=Nellie Gilad |studio=Lamut Le'at Ltd. |released={{Film date|df=yes|1969|||[[Israel]]}} |runtime=82 Minutes |country=[[Cinema of Israel|Israel]] |language=[[Hebrew language|Hebrew]]}} '''''A Woman's Case''''' ({{lang-he|'''מקרה אישה'''}}, [[romanization of Hebrew|tr.]] '''''Mikreh Isha''''') is a [[1969 in film|1969]] [[black and white]] [[cinema of Israel|Israeli]] [[independent film|independent]] [[underground film|underground]] [[experimental film|experimental]] [[drama (film and television)|dramatic]] [[art film]], the first [[cinema of Israel|Israeli]] film to be screened at the [[30th Venice International Film Festival|Venice Film Festival]], directed by [[Jacques Katmor]], and, usually, categorized as belonging to the [[bohemianism|bohemian]]/[[counterculture]] and [[anarchism|anarchistic]] {{ill|New Sensitivity|he|הרגישות החדשה}} movement.<ref>{{cite news|last=Shem-Or|first=Mirit|script-title=he:„'''מקרה אישה'''” בפסטיבל ונציה|trans-title=''A Woman's Case'' at the [[30th Venice International Film Festival|Venice Film Festival]]|date=2 December 1969|url=http://jpress.org.il/Olive/APA/NLI_heb/SharedView.Article.aspx?href=DAV%2F1969%2F09%2F02&id=Ar00600&sk=B0BE2A41|language=Hebrew|work=[[Davar]]|location=Tel Aviv|access-date=3 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Krishek|first=Tzvi|date=1 January 1970|script-title=he:מקרה סרט|trans-title=A Film's Case|url=http://jpress.org.il/Olive/APA/NLI_heb/SharedView.Article.aspx?href=MAR%2F1970%2F01%2F01&id=Ar02103&sk=47AD5A02|language=Hebrew|work=[[Maariv (newspaper)|Maariv]]|location=Tel Aviv|access-date=3 April 2017}}</ref> The film was released on [[DVD]] by [[NMC Music]].<ref>{{cite AV media|url=http://www.nmcunited.co.il/Content/MovieDetails.php?MovieId=21315|script-title=he:'''מקרה אישה'''|trans-title=A Woman's Case|people=[[Jacques Katmor|Katmor, Jacques]]|location=Ramat HaSharon|publisher=[[NMC Music]]|language=Hebrew|accessdate=4 April 2017|id=6214315|format=DVD|oclc=436441730|date=11 January 2009}}</ref> Cinematographer and coscreenwriter [[Amnon Salomon]] stated, during an interview, held late in life, that the film's origin is in Katmor's early exhibition, dealing with the female body, and, that no commercial motivations were held by the filmmakers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ictd.co.il/%D7%90%D7%9E%D7%A0%D7%95%D7%9F-%D7%A1%D7%9C%D7%95%D7%9E%D7%95%D7%9F/%D7%90%D7%99%D7%A9%D7%99%D7%95%D7%AA|script-title=he:אמנון סלומון|trans-title=[[Amnon Salomon]]|last=Parkhomovsky|first=Marat|date=7 December 2010|website=''[[:he:מאגר העדויות של הקולנוע הישראלי|Israeli Cinema Testimonial Database]]''|language=Hebrew|access-date=12 May 2017}}</ref>
==Synopsis== This modernist and non-linear film, influenced by the [[French New Wave]], and, especially, by films such as ''[[Jules and Jim]]'' and ''[[Breathless (1960 film)|Breathless]]'', tells the story of an advertiser (Yossi Spector), in his forties, who, meets Helit ({{ill|Helit Yeshurun|he|הלית ישורון}}), a model, in her twenties, and, together, the two spend a day in [[Tel Aviv]] and [[Jerusalem]], The model leads the advertiser into cafés and drug-fueled orgies, while, he leads her into the workshops of sculptors, so, that they could create sculptures, modeled on her body, out of [[gypsum]]. While she tries to liberate his mind, he attempts to stay where he is. The film ends with the advertiser strangling Helit to death, during a [[sadomasochism|sadomasochistic]] session.<ref>{{cite news|last=Levy Ben-Zakai|first=Talila|date=9 October 1969|script-title=he:הלית|trans-title=Helit|url=http://jpress.org.il/Olive/APA/NLI_heb/SharedView.Article.aspx?href=MAR%2F1969%2F10%2F09&id=Ar02101&sk=0339248E|language=Hebrew|work=[[Maariv (newspaper)|Maariv]]|location=Tel Aviv|access-date=3 April 2017}}</ref>
==Reception== ''[[Maariv (newspaper)|Maariv]]'' compared the film to the works of [[James Joyce]], [[Jean-Luc Godard]], and, [[Michelangelo Antonioni]], with the acting of {{ill|Helit Yeshurun|he|הלית ישורון}} being compared to that of [[Monica Vitti]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Porath|first=Yoram|date=3 July 1969|script-title=he:כתבה על עשיית הסרט|trans-title=A Report on the Film's Making|url=http://jpress.org.il/Olive/APA/NLI_heb/SharedView.Article.aspx?href=MAR%2F1969%2F07%2F03&id=Ar01902&sk=89D1DF22|language=Hebrew|work=[[Maariv (newspaper)|Maariv]]|location=Tel Aviv|access-date=3 April 2017}}</ref> writer [[Yoram Kaniuk]] wrote that the film is a critique of the horrors of the modern world,<ref>{{cite news|last=Kaniuk|first=Yoram|author-link=Yoram Kaniuk|script-title=he:על הסרט „'''מקרה אישה'''”|trans-title=On the Film ''A Woman's Case'' (Part I)|date=5 December 1969|url=http://jpress.org.il/Olive/APA/NLI_heb/SharedView.Article.aspx?href=DAV%2F1969%2F12%2F05&id=Ar00708&sk=3CEB3FFB|language=Hebrew|work=[[Davar]]|location=Tel Aviv|access-date=3 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Kaniuk|first=Yoram|author-link=Yoram Kaniuk|script-title=he:על הסרט „'''מקרה אישה'''”|trans-title=On the Film ''A Woman's Case'' (Part II)|date=5 December 1969|url=http://jpress.org.il/Olive/APA/NLI_heb/SharedView.Article.aspx?href=DAV%2F1969%2F12%2F05&id=Ar00911&sk=BCA458B4|language=Hebrew|work=[[Davar]]|location=Tel Aviv|access-date=3 April 2017}}</ref> and, ''[[Davar]]'' compared the film to painting.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=he:מראשו של צייר אל הבד|trans-title=From a Painter's Mind to the Cloth|date=28 November 1969|url=http://idea.cinema.co.il/ideawebinter/multimedia_11/0235/02350427.pdf|language=Hebrew|work=[[Davar]]|location=Tel Aviv|access-date=3 April 2017}}</ref> The film, however, was a commercial failure, with only 38,000 tickets sold, due to its highly avant-garde nature.<ref>{{cite news|last=Rappaport|first=Azaria|date=26 October 1969|script-title=he:אמנות – ליחידה־סגולה בלבד?|trans-title=Art – Only for the Privileged?|url=http://jpress.org.il/Olive/APA/NLI_Heb/SharedView.Article.aspx?parm=%2FZBcyTM2efPLRDKhPPbd2unqN7VZ8BoykBW0zPaiEYCZWs1JND2eQ1H%2FfmU6UGLkYw%3D%3D&mode=image&href=MAR%2f1969%2f11%2f26&page=10&rtl=true|language=Hebrew|work=[[Maariv (newspaper)|Maariv]]|location=Tel Aviv|access-date=3 April 2017}}</ref> [[University of Haifa]] sociologist, Prof. Dr. {{ill|Oz Almog (sociologist)|lt=Oz Almog|he|עוז אלמוג}}, wrote that film's main theme is the independent woman's, unsuccessful, attempt to free the man, from the shackles of his masculinity, and, noted that it was one of the first [[cinema of Israel|Israeli]] films to express their director's personal view.<ref>{{cite book|last=Almog|first=Prof. Dr. Oz|date=2004|script-title=he:'''פרידה משרוליק: שינוי ערכים באליטה הישראלית'''|trans-title=Farewell to “[[Srulik]]:” Changing Values Among the Israeli Elite|volume=II|pages=[https://books.google.co.il/books?id=9YhtAAAAMAAJ&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22%D7%A9%D7%A0%D7%95%D7%A6%D7%A8%D7%95+%D7%91%D7%A9%D7%A0%D7%95%D7%AA+%D7%94%D7%A9%D7%99%D7%A9%D7%99%D7%9D+%D7%95%D7%94%D7%A9%D7%91%D7%A2%D7%99%D7%9D%22 659], [https://books.google.co.il/books?id=9YhtAAAAMAAJ&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22%D7%90%D7%A1%D7%AA%D7%99+%D7%96%D7%91%D7%A7%D7%95%22 886], [https://books.google.co.il/books?id=9YhtAAAAMAAJ&dqsearchwithinvolume&q=%22%D7%A9%D7%91%D7%95+%D7%90%D7%99%D7%A9%D7%94+%D7%A2%D7%A6%D7%9E%D7%90%D7%99%D7%AA%22 915], and, [https://books.google.co.il/books?id=9YhtAAAAMAAJ&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22%D7%A9%D7%9C+%D7%96%27%D7%90%D7%A7+%D7%9E%D7%95%D7%A8%D7%99%22 1278]|location=Haifa and Or Yehuda|language=Hebrew|publisher=[[:he:הוצאת הספרים של אוניברסיטת חיפה|Haifa University Press]] and [[Kinneret Zmora-Bitan Dvir]]|isbn=9789653110519|oclc=56795640}}</ref>
