{{Unreferenced|date=November 2007}}A '''Bachelor of Human Kinetics''' ('''BHk''' or '''BHKin''') or '''Bachelor of Science in Human Kinetics''' ('''BScHK''') is a four-year [[academic degree]] awarded by a [[university]] upon the completion of a program of study of [[Human kinetics]]. Specializations within this degree can include: [[Physical Therapy | Athletic Therapy]], [[Kinesiology]], [[Physical Education]], [[Recreation]], and [[Sport management]].

