The '''Punjabi Language Movement''' (PLM) is a linguistic movement in [[Punjab, Pakistan]] aimed at reviving the [[Punjabi language]], art, culture and literature in [[Pakistan]].<ref name="Report 2011">{{cite web | last=Report | first=Staff | title=‘Punjab wants its mother tongue back’ | website=Pakistan Today | date=21 February 2011 | url=http://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2011/02/21/city/lahore/punjab-wants-its-mother-tongue-back/ | accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Brown|first1=Michael Edward|title=Fighting Words: Language Policy and Ethnic Relations in Asia|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=fcoDezu1ABoC&pg=PA68&lpg=PA68&dq=Punjabi+Language+Movement+pakistan&source=bl&ots=7jCUQZ1Q_A&sig=APZQYqDZQ46A7DD9xGa5xBf0PpM&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiR5cKRjp7MAhWIVZQKHcIdB8k4ChDoAQgaMAA#v=onepage&q=Punjabi%20Language%20Movement%20pakistan&f=false}}</ref><ref name="Kamal 2015">{{cite web | last=Kamal | first=Neel | title=A march for Punjabi revival in Pak's Punjab | website=The Times of India | date=14 September 2015 | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/A-march-for-Punjabi-revival-in-Paks-Punjab/articleshow/48951621.cms | accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref><ref name="Soofi 2015">{{cite web | last=Soofi | first=Mushtaq | title=Punjab Notes: Mother language, people and politicians | website=DAWN.COM | date=27 February 2015 | url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1166216 | accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref><ref>[http://www.punjabilanguagemovement.org// Punjabi Language Movement]</ref> The [[Punjabi people]] constitute the largest ethnic group in Pakistan though [[Urdu]] is the national language<ref name="Service 2016">{{cite web | last=Service | first=Tribune News | title=Thousands to march for Punjabi in Lahore | website=http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/punjab/thousands-to-march-for-punjabi-in-lahore/198233.html | date=19 February 2016 | url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/punjab/thousands-to-march-for-punjabi-in-lahore/198233.html | accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref> and unlike [[Punjab, India|Indian Punjab]] (where reading/writing Punjabi language is compulsory at every level from 2008<ref name="Zee News 2008">{{cite web | title=Punjab Cabinet Okays to amend Punjabi official language Act | website=Zee News | date=3 September 2008 | url=http://zeenews.india.com/home/punjab-cabinet-okays-to-amend-punjabi-official-language-act_466443.html | language=la | accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref> alongside a special [[Punjabi University]] at [[Patiala]]), Punjabi itself does not have an official status. The PLM's ideologies are based on [[Punjabi nationalism]].
